     when it is delayed.  Maybe its vCPU is preempted or something.<br /><br />Where exactly do you see "increment -&gt;rcu_users"<br /><br />There are _no_ users that can increment rcu_users. The thing is<br />initialized to '2' when the process is created, and nobody ever<br />increments it. EVER.<br /><br />It's only ever decremented, and when it hits zero we know that both<br />users are gone, and we start the rcu-delayed free.<br /><br />            Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
